# Code Separation Rules

Always maintain strict separation of concerns:
- **No inline CSS** in HTML (no `style=""` attributes)
- **No embedded CSS** in HTML (no `<style>` tags)
- **No embedded JavaScript** in HTML (no `<script>` tags with inline code)

Use external files only:
- CSS: Link via `<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">`
- JavaScript: Link via `<script src="script.js"></script>`